<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3945035>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Left maxillary (above) and mandibular (below) toothrows of P. jagorii, XS.53 (left), P. atrox, PSU-M 05.11 (centre), and K. kachinensis, CMR-28 (right). (i): I3, much reduced in Phoniscus; (ii): antero-internal elongation of P3 in P. jagorii; (iii): P3 larger and rectangular in P. jagorii in comparison to P. atrox; (iv): P3 narrow in Phoniscus, broader in Kerivoula. Scale = 2 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3945035/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

